  ---\
  Why MeshGraphNet and not M3GNet for our problem\
\
  M3GNet is designed for atomistic systems \'97 discrete atoms at crystallographic positions with periodic boundary\
  conditions. It captures 3-body angular interactions because bond angles matter for crystal stability.\
\
  Our problem is a continuum fluid domain:\
  - No atoms \'97 just continuous space discretised into 333K cells\
  - No periodicity \'97 enclosed showerhead geometry\
  - Need spatial field prediction at every point, not a single scalar\
  - Multi-physics: flow + heat + species simultaneously \
  \
  MeshGraphNet was specifically designed for CFD mesh prediction \'97 it maps directly to our problem.\
\
  ---\
  What our MultiHeadMGN adds on top of standard MGN\
  \
  Standard MGN has one output head. We added:\
\
  Shared encoder (22-dim input \uc0\u8594  256-dim latent)\
           \uc0\u8595 \
    15 \'d7 MGNProcessor  (message passing with residuals + LayerNorm)\
           \uc0\u8595 \
      \uc0\u9484 \u9472 \u9472 \u9472 \u9472 \u9472 \u9472 \u9472 \u9472 \u9472 \u9472 \u9472 \u9472 \u9516 \u9472 \u9472 \u9472 \u9472 \u9472 \u9472 \u9472 \u9472 \u9472 \u9472 \u9472 \u9472 \u9516 \u9472 \u9472 \u9472 \u9472 \u9472 \u9472 \u9472 \u9472 \u9472 \u9472 \u9472 \u9472 \u9472 \u9472 \u9488 \
    Flow head   Heat head  Species head\
    [Ux,Uy,Uz,p]   [T]        [TMA]\
\
  The multi-head design lets each physics domain learn its own output mapping while sharing the geometric\
  understanding encoded in the shared latent space.\
\
  ---\
  The connection to your M3GNet experience\
  \
  The message-passing framework is identical conceptually \'97 you already understand it from M3GNet. The key\
  difference is what the nodes and edges represent:\
\
  - M3GNet: node = Al/O atom at (x,y,z), edge = bond, message = atomic force contribution\
  - MultiHeadMGN: node = fluid cell at (x,y,z), edge = geometric neighbour, message = local flow field\
  contribution\
\
  Same mathematical machinery, completely different physical interpretation. Your M3GNet background is actually\
  a strong foundation for understanding what we built \'97 the architectural intuition transfers directly.\
